  "period_agreement_label": "2. Period of Agreement",
  "period_agreement_desc": "This Agreement shall take effect upon activation of the Customer’s account or mobile telephone connection to the Service and shall remain in force until terminated in accordance with these Terms and Conditions. CCP reserves the right to use any Information provided from the date of disclosure by the Customer.",
  "account_security_label": "3. Account, Security, and Payment",
  "account_security_desc": "To access the Services, the Customer must register an Account by providing accurate and complete details, including identification information (NRIC/passport), contact details, and a secure password.",
  "account_register_label": "By registering, the Customer expressly:",
  "account_register_1": "1. Consents to the processing of personal data for the purpose of service provision",
  "account_register_2": "2. Undertakes to pay all applicable fees, charges, and taxes associated with the Services",
  "additional_provisions_label": "Additional provisions:",
  "additional_provisions_1": "Tokens and Monthly Passes purchased are non-refundable and non-transferable.",
  "additional_provisions_2": "Tokens shall expire three (3) years from the purchase date.",
  "additional_provisions_3": "In cases of bank delays or system disruptions, CCP will coordinate with municipal councils or concessionaires to resolve issues promptly.",
  "additional_provisions_4": "Any disputes concerning charges must be submitted in writing within fourteen (14) days of the billing date. If no objection is received, the bill shall be deemed accurate and binding.",
  "additional_provisions_5": "CCP reserves the right to recover unpaid sums, including legal costs, and statements signed by CCP officers shall constitute conclusive evidence of debt.",
  "customer_responsibilities_label": "4. Customer Responsibilities",
  "customer_shall": "The Customer shall:",
  "customer_responsibilities_1": "Use the Service responsibly and at their own risk.",
  "customer_responsibilities_2": "Report fraud, unauthorised use, or irregularities within 24 hours of discovery.",
  "customer_responsibilities_3": "Ensure the security of devices and software used for accessing the Service.",
  "customer_responsibilities_4": "Not misuse the Service for unlawful purposes, third-party rights infringement, harassment, or spamming.",
  "customer_responsibilities_5": "Comply with all technical upgrades, system changes, or instructions issued by CCP.",
  "customer_responsibilities_6": "Accept responsibility for verifying whether their use of the Service breaches applicable laws or codes of conduct.",
  "ccp_rights_liabilities_label": "5. Rights and Liabilities of CCP",
  "ccp_rights_liabilities_1": "CCP shall not be liable for losses or damages (direct, indirect, or consequential) arising from:",
  "ccp_rights_liabilities_1a": "Service modifications, interruptions, or suspension.",
  "ccp_rights_liabilities_1b": "Malfunctions or defects in devices, mobile telephones, or the CCP System.",
  "ccp_rights_liabilities_1c": "Customer’s inability to access or utilise the Service.",
  "ccp_rights_liabilities_1d": "Data loss, viruses, or unauthorised access outside CCP’s reasonable control.",
  "ccp_rights_liabilities_2": "CCP reserves the right to:",
  "ccp_rights_liabilities_2a": "Suspend, modify, or terminate Services for system maintenance, regulatory requirements, or suspected fraud.",
  "ccp_rights_liabilities_2b": "Amend these Terms and Conditions at its discretion. Continued use of Services constitutes acceptance of amendments.",
  "ccp_rights_liabilities_2c": "Retain Tokens for settlement of outstanding dues upon termination.",
  "ccp_rights_liabilities_3": "The Customer shall indemnify CCP against all claims, actions, or losses resulting from misuse of the Service.",
  "force_majeure_label": "6. Force Majeure",
  "force_majeure_desc": "CCP shall not be held liable for failure or delay in performance resulting from events beyond its reasonable control, including natural disasters, war, civil unrest, industrial disputes, government directives, or other unforeseen circumstances.",
  "waiver_misc_label": "7. Waiver and Miscellaneous Provisions:",
  "waiver_misc_1": "Failure by CCP to exercise a right shall not constitute a waiver of that right.",
  "waiver_misc_2": "This Agreement is governed by the laws of Malaysia, and disputes shall fall under the exclusive jurisdiction of the Malaysian courts.",
  "waiver_misc_3": "Notices may be delivered by hand, post, email, SMS, or application messaging.",
  "waiver_misc_4": "The Customer may not assign rights under this Agreement without prior consent, CCP may assign obligations at its discretion.",
  "waiver_misc_5": "Invalid provisions shall not affect the enforceability of the remainder of the Agreement.",
  "waiver_misc_6": "CCP reserves the right to verify customer information and reject registrations without liability.",
  "data_protection_label": "8. Data Protection Obligations",
  "data_protection_desc": "CCP is committed to compliance with the Personal Data Protection Act 2010. All personal data will be processed in accordance with CCP’s Privacy Notice, which forms an integral part of these Terms. By registering or continuing use of the Service, the Customer consents to such processing and disclosure of data as required for service provision.",
  "disclaimer_label": "9. Disclaimer",
  "disclaimer_1": "All content within the CCP System is protected by copyright © CityCarPark 2016–2025. Reproduction or distribution is prohibited without written consent.",
  "disclaimer_2": "“CCP” and associated marks are registered trademarks of CityCarPark. Other product names are trademarks of their respective owners.",
  "disclaimer_3": "Information is provided “as is” without warranties of accuracy, completeness, or fitness for purpose.",
  "disclaimer_4": "CCP is not responsible for third-party content or external websites linked through its system.",
  "disclaimer_5": "CCP shall not be liable for damages (direct, indirect, or consequential) resulting from use of its Services.",
  "privacyPolicy": "Privacy Policy",
  "introduction_label": "1. Introduction",
  "introduction_desc": "This Privacy Data Notice is issued to inform you that your personal information is being collected and processed by, or on behalf of, CityCarPark (hereinafter referred to as “CCP,” “we”, “our”, or “us”). For the purposes of this Notice, the terms “personal data” and “processing” shall carry the definitions provided under the Personal Data Protection Act 2010 (PDPA).",
  "categories_label": "2. Categories of Personal Data Collected",
  "categories_desc": "CCP collects only such personal information as is necessary for the proper administration of our services and for the fulfilment of legitimate business purposes. The categories of personal data we may obtain include, but are not limited to:",
  "identification_label": "Identification and contact details:",
  "identification_desc": "Full name, date of birth, national identification number or passport number (including copies, where necessary), e-mail address, telephone number, and, where relevant, bank account or payment card details.",
  "transaction_label": "Transactional information:",
  "transaction_desc": "Records of parking payments, token top-ups, and other transactions undertaken through our digital or physical platforms.",
  "digital_label": "Digital interaction data:",
  "digital_desc": "Information gathered from your use of our mobile applications, websites, and online platforms (including referring websites, browsing behaviour, content accessed, duration of visits, and analytical data from tools such as Google Analytics).",
  "feedback_label": "Feedback and communications:",
  "feedback_desc": "Responses submitted via feedback forms, surveys, or customer support interactions.",
  "marketing_label": "Marketing and promotional data:",
  "marketing_desc": "Details provided during participation in campaigns, contests, loyalty programmes, or partnerships undertaken by CCP or its authorised affiliates.",
  "third_party_label": "Third-party information:",
  "third_party_desc": "Personal data obtained from external sources such as financial institutions, credit reporting agencies, or other entities legally permitted to disclose such information.",
  "purposes_label": "3. Purposes of Processing",
  "purposes_desc": "Your personal data may be processed for one or more of the following purposes:",
  "account_service_label": "Account and service administration:",
  "account_service_desc": "Registering, verifying, and maintaining your account and identity",
  "services_label": "Provision of services:",
  "services_desc": "Facilitating transactions, processing payments, issuing receipts, and maintaining records for financial, audit, and regulatory purposes.",
  "regulatory_label": "Regulatory compliance:",
  "regulatory_desc": "Fulfilling legal, anti-money laundering, and risk management obligations.",
  "communication_label": "Communication:",
  "communication_desc": "Corresponding with you regarding enquiries, complaints, updates, or administrative notices.",
  "personalisation_label": "Personalisation:",
  "personalisation_desc": "Enhancing user experience on our platforms, including targeted content, advertisements, and loyalty programmes.",
  "research_label": "Research and analytics:",
  "research_desc": "Conducting market surveys, customer profiling, statistical analysis, and service improvement studies.",
  "marketing_outreach_label": "Marketing and outreach:",
  "marketing_outreach_desc": "Providing information about products, services, programmes, or promotional activities organised or sponsored by CCP or its affiliates.",
  "data_management_label": "Data management:",
  "data_management_desc": "Storing, backing up, and securing data (whether locally or internationally) for operational continuity and disaster recovery.",
  "legal_disclosure_label": "Legal disclosure:",
  "legal_disclosure_desc": "Complying with statutory, regulatory, or judicial requirements, or making disclosures mandated by law.",
  "general_business_label": "General business purposes:",
  "general_business_desc": "Supporting the management, maintenance, and strategic development of CCP’s services.",
  "sources_label": "4. Sources of Personal Data",
  "sources_desc": "Your data may be collected directly from you through interactions such as:",
  "sources_account": "Account registration or subscription to services.",
  "sources_events": "Participation in events, surveys, contests, or loyalty programmes.",
  "sources_purchase": "Purchase of tokens, passes, or related services through CCP platforms.",
  "sources_communications": "Communications with our customer service representatives.",
  "sources_feedback": "Submissions of feedback or complaints.",
  "sources_third_party": "Additionally, CCP may obtain your information indirectly from authorised third parties, including business partners, subsidiaries, financial institutions, or public directories where you have provided consent.",
  "data_subject_label": "5. Your Rights as a Data Subject",
  "data_subject_desc": "Under the PDPA, you are entitled to exercise the following rights in respect of your personal data:",
  "right_access_label": "Access: ",
  "right_access_desc": "to request confirmation and information about your personal data being processed (Section 30(2) PDPA).",
  "right_correction_label": "Correction: ",
  "right_correction_right": "to request rectification of inaccurate, incomplete, or outdated information.",
  "right_restriction_label": "Restriction: ",
  "right_restriction_desc": "to limit the processing of your personal data under circumstances permitted by law.",
  "right_withdrawal_label": "Withdrawal: ",
  "right_withdrawal_desc": "to opt out of receiving marketing or promotional communications by following the unsubscribe instructions provided in our correspondence.",
  "right_deletion_label": "Deletion: ",
  "right_deletion_desc": "to request removal of your data from our systems, subject to statutory exceptions.",
  "data_requests_contact": "All requests or complaints should be submitted in writing to cs@citycarpark.my. Please note that CCP may lawfully refuse certain requests in circumstances permitted by the PDPA, and reasons for such refusal will be communicated within the statutory timeline.",
  "disclosure_label": "6. Disclosure of Data to Third Parties",
  "disclosure_desc": "CCP may disclose your personal data to the following categories of recipients:",
  "disclosure_companies": "Companies within the CCP corporate group (including subsidiaries, related entities, and shareholders).",
  "disclosure_advisers": "Professional advisers, agents, contractors, service providers, vendors, and business partners.",
  "disclosure_banks": "Banks, financial institutions, and insurance companies involved in facilitating transactions.",
  "disclosure_successors": "Successors or parties involved in corporate exercises, such as mergers, acquisitions, or restructuring.",
  "disclosure_government": "Government agencies, regulators, municipal councils, and statutory bodies, whether domestic or foreign, where legally required.",
  "disclosure_confidential": "All third parties receiving your data will be expected to treat it as confidential and use it solely for legitimate purposes aligned with this Notice.",
  "data_subjects_label": "7. Obligations of Data Subjects",
  "data_subjects_desc": "You are required to ensure that the personal data provided to CCP is complete, accurate, and up to date. Failure to supply such information may impede our ability to deliver services effectively. You are also expected to promptly update us regarding any changes to your personal data.",
  "security_label": "8. Security of Personal Data",
  "security_desc": "CCP is committed to safeguarding personal data through appropriate administrative, technical, and physical security measures, including but not limited to encryption, firewalls, and secure socket layers. While we strive to ensure robust protection, we acknowledge that no system can guarantee absolute security. CCP shall not be held liable for unauthorised access or breaches beyond our reasonable control.",
  "retention_label": "9. Retention of Data",
  "retention_desc": "Your personal data will be retained only for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes outlined in this Notice, or as required by applicable laws and regulations.",
  "amendments_label": "10. Amendments to this Notice",
  "amendments_desc": "CCP reserves the right to revise this Privacy Data Notice from time to time. Any amendments will be communicated via our mobile application or other communication channels deemed appropriate by CCP.",
  "language_label": "11. Language and Interpretation",
  "language_desc": "In the event of discrepancies between the English version of this Notice and its Bahasa Malaysia counterpart, the English version shall prevail.",
  "external_websites_label": "12. External Websites",
  "external_websites_desc": "Where our platform contains links to third-party websites, please note that this Privacy Notice does not apply once you leave CCP’s digital environment. CCP does not control such websites and shall not be responsible for their privacy practices. Users are encouraged to review the privacy policies of external sites before providing personal data.",
